Definition: any of numerous plants of the genus Gladiolus native chiefly to tropical and South Africa having sword-shaped leaves and one-sided spikes of brightly colored funnel-shaped flowers
Example: widely cultivated
Synonyms: gladiola, glad, sword_lily, iridaceous_plant, genus_Gladiolus, m, any, of, numerous, plants, the, genus, Gladiolus, native, chiefly, to, tropical, and, South, Africa, having, sword-shaped, leaves, one-sided, spikes, brightly, colored, funnel-shaped, flowers, widely, cultivated
Category: noun.plant
